      "url": "https://newatlas.com/3d-printing/recyclable-3d-printing-resin/",
      "title": "[New Atlas] Exacting atomic-scale 3D printing is adding a critical capability",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/b1aacc0/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3828x2010+0+271/resize/1200x630!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com%2Fe9%2F91%2Fbb04df4b4e148255de513cdf5826%2Fdepositphotos-194185574-xl.jpeg&amp;na.image_optimisation=0\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<p><img alt=\"Although SLA (stereolithography) 3D printing produces some very nice-looking results, any resin wasted during the process can't be recycled\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/7800be6/2147483647/strip/true/crop/3828x2552+0+0/resize/1440x960!/format/webp/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com%2Fe9%2F91%2Fbb04df4b4e148255de513cdf5826%2Fdepositphotos-194185574-xl.jpeg\" /><p>Whether you’re constructing homes through your 3D-printing company, creating RPG tabletop terrains and cosplay weapons through your garage-based modeling operation, or providing disaster relief and building structures in distant locales or even on other planets, you don’t want to waste your medium. On Earth, that’d be financially and ecologically expensive, but in space, on the Moon, or on Mars, depleting your printing resource could be a disaster.</p><p><a href=\"https://newatlas.com/3d-printing/recyclable-3d-printing-resin/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/3d-printing/\">3D Printing</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/manufacturing/\">Manufacturing</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/engineering/\">Engineering</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/yokohama-national-university/\" rel=\"tag\">Yokohama National University</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/recycling/\" rel=\"tag\">Recycling</a></p>",
      "date_published": "2026-07-19T14:03:00+00:00",
      "authors": [
